<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> short change • small change</xh5><p> <i>short change—</i>a less than the correct amount of money given back to a customer: After several rounds of drinks had been served, Sullivan accused Cook of giving him <u>short change</u>.</p><p><i>small change—</i>coins or bills of low denomination: It is always best to have some <u>small change</u> on you, locals often have no change of larger bills.</p> </entry>
